{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe live Jira/LLM external tier (`tests/external/`) runs only on `workflow_dispatch`\n(`.github/workflows/external-integration.yml`), which sets `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` and maps\n`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`/`OPENAI_API_KEY` but **no `JIRA_*` secrets** and does **not install the\n`acli` binary** — and `test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py::_live_jira_ready()` gates on BOTH\n(`creds and shutil.which(\"acli\")`). So the live Jira round-trip can only ever SKIP: Jira\nAPI/SDK drift merges through normal CI with no real integration signal, and nothing fails a\nrun in which the whole external tier silently skips. VALIDATED.\n\nCorrection to the earlier framing: the live test is NOT read-only — it calls `create_issue`\ntwice + `set_relationship`, then in a `try/finally` deletes every artifact it created (links\nthen issues). It makes REAL, self-cleaning Jira mutations against whatever project the creds\npoint at, so it requires a DEDICATED disposable test project, not a shared one.\n\n## What\n1. **Workflow** (`external-integration.yml`): add an `on.schedule` trigger with the exact cron\n   `0 6 * * 1` (Mondays 06:00 UTC, weekly) alongside `workflow_dispatch`, and MIRROR the\n   established `reconcile-bridge.yml` convention\n   EXACTLY (not an ad-hoc variant):\n   - Jira env, sourced the SAME way reconcile-bridge does: `JIRA_URL: ${{ vars.JIRA_URL }}`,\n     `JIRA_USER: ${{ vars.JIRA_USER }}` (repo VARIABLES, not secrets), and\n     `JIRA_API_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.JIRA_API_TOKEN }}` (the only secret).\n   - the `acli` install, reusing reconcile-bridge's THREE companion steps verbatim in shape:\n     the `cache-acli` cache step, the `Download + verify + install acli` step (pinned\n     `vars.ACLI_VERSION` + `vars.ACLI_SHA256`, sha256-checked), AND the `Add acli to PATH and\n     authenticate` step exactly as reconcile-bridge does it: `sudo ln -sf \"$HOME/.acli/acli\"\n     /usr/local/bin/acli` (symlink the binary into the on-PATH `/usr/local/bin`, NOT\n     `$GITHUB_PATH`), then `echo \"$JIRA_API_TOKEN\" | acli jira auth login --site \"$JIRA_URL\"\n     --email \"$JIRA_USER\" --token`. Without this step `shutil.which(\"acli\")` and the live auth\n     both fail, so the Jira tests still skip.\n2. **Fail-on-all-skip canary** (`tests/external/conftest.py`): add a pytest session hook that,\n   when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is truthy (a real scheduled/dispatch run), REPORTS the\n   external-tier executed-vs-skipped counts and FAILS the session when the LIVE tier did not\n   actually exercise anything. Threshold (precise, because some external tests are always-on\n   guards that need no credentials): the hook fails iff (a) at least one external test SKIPPED\n   with a reason indicating a missing live prerequisite (reason matching, case-insensitively,\n   `cred`/`acli`/`live`/`api.token`) AND (b) ZERO credential-gated live tests EXECUTED\n   (passed or failed) — where the always-on guard tests that carry NO credential skip (e.g.\n   `test_external_tier_allows_model_requests`, which needs no creds and never skips) are\n   EXCLUDED from the executed-live count, so their unconditional execution cannot mask an\n   all-skip live tier. When `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset (the default suite, where the tier is\n   intentionally inert via the opt-in guard), the hook is a no-op.\n3. **Tests**:\n   - a behavioral test of the fail-on-all-skip hook: an all-skipped external session with\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` makes the hook signal failure; ≥1 executed passes; unset\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is a no-op.\n   - a config-as-artifact test asserting `external-integration.yml` declares an `on.schedule`\n     trigger, maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` into the external job env, AND\n     installs `acli` / puts it on PATH (a drift guard mirroring the repo's YAML-artifact tests).\n\n## Scope\n- `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml` — schedule + JIRA_* env + acli install/PATH.\n- `tests/external/conftest.py` — fail-on-all-skip session hook + executed/skipped report.\n- A test module (e.g. `tests/unit/test_external_canary.py`) — the hook behavior + workflow wiring.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The workflow declares `on.schedule` with cron `0 6 * * 1`; sources `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`\n      from `vars.*` and `JIRA_API_TOKEN` from `secrets.*` (matching reconcile-bridge.yml); and\n      installs `acli` + symlinks it onto PATH + authenticates (the cache / download-verify-install\n      / add-to-PATH-and-authenticate steps). A config-as-artifact test pins the cron, the Jira\n      env wiring, and the acli PATH/auth step.\n- [ ] The conftest FAILS an external session (with `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1`) when ≥1 external test\n      skipped for a missing live prerequisite AND zero credential-gated live tests executed\n      (always-on guard tests excluded from the executed count); it PASSES when a credential-gated\n      live test executed; and it is a no-op when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset — asserted by a\n      behavioral test of the hook over simulated session outcomes.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER` repo VARIABLES and the `JIRA_API_TOKEN`\n      SECRET, plus the `ACLI_VERSION`/`ACLI_SHA256` repo variables, are configured in the GitHub\n      repo, and a DEDICATED disposable Jira test project is provisioned for the self-cleaning\n      live mutations — these require GitHub repo-admin + a Jira project and cannot be done from\n      the code change; attested by the operator with the config evidence.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783812758094812001,"uuid":"0179a6c6-2ae8-48f5-8cd4-afdb35cd6f66"}